				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I've upgraded the spam protection from <a href="http://bbantispam.com/tc/" target="_blank" class="postlink">Textual Confirmation</a> to <a href="http://bbantispam.com/atc/" target="_blank" class="postlink">Advanced Textual Confirmation</a>. The former is more integrated to phpBB, but the latter is more general and works not only for phpBB.
<br />

<br />
As a side effect, even the already registered users have to answer a question. I hope it's not very hard.
<br />

<br />
Meanwhile, I've also switched off Links Rejector. It seems it isn't very important on this support forum. (But it works very well on another community forum, preventing even spam from humans!)
<br />

<br />
